OL,3,CHuge cost to the economy of work-
OL,4,Crelated ill health ` TUC
OL,6,FWork-related ill health is costing the
OL,7,Feconomy more than #415 million a week,
OL,8,Faccording to a report.
OL,10,FThe TUC said its analysis suggested
OL,11,Fthat the number of days lost because
OL,12,Fof health conditions such as stress,
OL,13,Fdepression and anxiety has increased
OL,14,Fby a third since 2010.
OL,16,FThe union organisation said that in
OL,17,F2023 to 2024, around 34 million
OL,18,Fworking days were lost to work-related
OL,19,Fill health, compared with 22 million
OL,20,Fin 2010.
