OL,6,F"That's why the government's
OL,7,FEmployment Rights Bill is so
OL,8,Fimportant. Cracking down on
OL,9,Fexploitative practices like zero-hours
OL,10,Fcontracts and giving people more
OL,11,Fsecurity will boost workers' health,
OL,12,Fwellbeing and productivity. It will
OL,13,Falso help more people stay in work.
OL,15,F"We need to turn the corner on
OL,16,FBritain's low-rights, low-pay economic
OL,17,Fmodel that has been tested to
OL,18,Fdestruction over the last 14 years."
